Environmental stochasticity or noise color was implemented as follows: The parameter θ*t = θt + ϕt, was the realized environmental state with noise ϕt = αϕt-1 + βξt. The autocorrelation coefficient α indicated the level of environmental correlation and therefore the noise color: − 1 < α < 0, blue noise; α = 0, white noise, and 0 < α < 1, red noise. Three scenarios of α were considered, based on Björklund et al. [25]: blue noise (α = − 0.7); white noise (α = 0), and red noise (α = 0.7). The parameter β determined the environmental variance, according to β = σ
