				\begin{document}$$ w^{\prime }i={wie}^{\left(1-\frac{N}{K}\right)} $$\end{document}w′i=wie1−NKwhere N is the population size and K, the carrying capacity. Each couple (partners i,j) produced a number of offspring randomly drawn from a Poisson distribution with expectancy λ = w’i + w’j.

The mean x of the distribution of mutation effect size was given by x = ε – y
